You are not full term until 39 weeks according to ACOG and March of Dimes so I wouldn't do a thing until then. After that, walking and staying active, staying calm and staying distracted generally works just fine. I was out shoveling snow the day before I went into labor at 40 weeks on the dot - because it needed to be done, not because I thought it would get things started. But I never took epo or castor oil, never had my membranes stripped, never bounced on a yoga ball. Just let it happen and it'll happen - nobody's ever been pregnant forever.

Agree with Geekmom1213 Just let it happen, baby will come when She or he is ready. Your considered full term at 38w, I rather go over and let my baby fully develop and come when she is ready, even if it makes me miserable.

I started my labor on my own at 36 weeks, but it was medically necessary.  I was scheduled to be enduce the next day due to preeclampsia and wanted a natural birth.  I would only suggest it if it was medically necessary. I wish i could carry full term.  It is a blessing. I've had a still born at 28 weeks, my daughter at 36 and my son at 34 all due to preeclampsia. I'm 28 weeks now praying i can carry this one full term.
